71 to 63 Dey Street (left) at, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner of Washington (right, street car thereon) showing at the corner the former Turf Exchange Hotel, No. 71, erected in 1879. This structure bears No. 179 on Washington Street; on which is shown Nos. 179 to 171, east side, south from Dey to and including Cortlandt Streets.

May 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

July 1, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, at a later date, excluding the view of Dey Street.
April 17, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
